Femme fatale Jenny Lewis has never sounded so passionate and her songs 
never so hard-hitting and acerbic as on her aptly titled solo disk, Acid 
Tongue. The album follows 2006&#039;s Rabbit Fur Coat (which Spin named among 
the best albums of that year) and a series of acclaimed albums with indie rock 
fave Rilo Kiley. Featuring collaborations with A Band Called She & Him and 
guest appearances by Elvis Costello and Chris Robinson of The Black Crowes, 
Acid Tongue proves to be wicked good.
